Some languages have this already. Specifically safety critical languages like Ada. Ever so slowly the entire industry is moving towards what ada had in 1983. Beyond
this you can use the spark annotations on top of ada to verify code does what it's expected to.<p>Here's some Ada range examples
 type My_Int is range 1..100;
 type byte is mod 2<i></i>8;
 type Sin_Values is digits 10
   range -1.0..1.0;<p>Then you can query the object for its range:
  z'range;
or see if it's even valid, useful for finding stray bits switched by cosmic rays - I'm serious here.
 if z'valid then
   dowhatever;
 else
   printwarning;
